{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a51cea8e99efb2b84","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Deep WEB research (WebSearch + WebFetch; cite URLs throughout). Do not answer from memory alone. Question: could a SMALL, LOCAL model (8B-class, e.g. qwen3:8b, on a 16 GB Apple-silicon Mac, one model at a time) ever autonomously write/extend/improve its OWN source code well enough to self-build — and what's the capability gap?\n\nResearch concretely:\n1. **Code capability of ~7-8B local models in 2025-2026**: SWE-bench Verified, LiveCodeBench, Aider/Polyglot scores for Qwen3-8B / Qwen2.5-Coder-7B/14B / DeepSeek-Coder / similar small models vs frontier (Claude/GPT). How far below frontier are small local models at real multi-file code edits that compile + pass tests? Concrete numbers.\n2. **The autonomy threshold**: what SWE-bench-ish success rate is needed for a self-improvement loop to make net-positive progress (more good commits than regressions)? Any analysis of when self-improvement loops stall or collapse with weak base models.\n3. **On-device training/distillation feasibility on 16 GB** (recap if found): LoRA/QLoRA on 8B via MLX — time, memory, quality — for a model to improve its own coding via self-generated + verified data. Self-training / self-rewarding / RLVR (RL from verifiable rewards) on small models locally: does it work, what's needed.\n4. **Bootstrapping strategies that reduce the base-capability bar**: test-time compute / best-of-N + a strong verifier (compiler + test suite) to lift a weak model's *effective* coding ability; evolutionary/population search over candidate edits gated by tests; using a stronger teacher to distill coding skill into the local model. How much can a rigorous verifier compensate for a weak generator?\n5. **Realistic outlook**: are small local models trending toward \"good enough to self-improve their own codebase,\" and on what timeline / with what techniques?\n\nEND WITH a concrete verdict for a 16 GB local \"Yogi\": is local self-coding feasible now / soon / far-off, the single biggest blocker, and the highest-leverage things to build so that WHEN local models cross the threshold the system can use them (verifier-gated edit loop, worktree isolation, test harness as fitness). Cite URLs. Return findings only; do not edit files."},"uuid":"f58e2256-1d0f-4cab-9874-ec26209fd96b","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:33:50.039Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
