ng strategies that reduce the base-capability bar (test-time compute / best-of-N + strong verifier = compiler+tests; evolutionary/population search gated by tests; teacher distillation — how much a rigorous verifier compensates for a weak generator). (5) Realistic outlook and timeline. END with a concrete verdict for a 16 GB local \\\"Yogi\\\": feasible now/soon/far-off, single biggest blocker, highest-leverage things to build (verifier-gated edit loop, worktree isolation, test harness as fitness). Cite URLs throughout.\" })"}]},"isMeta":true,"uuid":"92f78743-6c4d-421b-818e-309bf63a7720","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:33:59.376Z","sourceToolUseID":"toolu_01KwQFHgzWS4YSGTt1wyvE88","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
