{"parentUuid":"b1b6dab3-44c9-47e1-8653-e8d2837c6cff","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a51cea8e99efb2b84","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01WL7qTcr2xSPA9pvHKa5Cii","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019BSUqJUJq9m9JfiSfh2XT1","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Verifier-gated bootstrapping strategies","prompt":"You are a web research agent. Use WebSearch and WebFetch (load them via ToolSearch query \"select:WebSearch,WebFetch\" first if not available). The current date is June 2026.\n\nRESEARCH ANGLE: Bootstrapping strategies that let a WEAK generator achieve strong effective coding ability via a strong verifier — i.e. how much a rigorous verifier (compiler + test suite) can compensate for a weak generator.\n\nResearch concretely:\n- Test-time compute / inference scaling: best-of-N, repeated sampling, \"Large Language Monkeys\" (Brown et al. — repeated sampling, coverage scales with samples), self-consistency. Concrete: how much does pass@k improve over pass@1 for code when you can verify? Numbers showing a small model with many samples + a verifier approaching or matching a bigger model's pass@1.\n- The generator-verifier gap: verification is easier than generation; strong verifier amplifies weak generator. Any papers quantifying this.\n- Evolutionary / population search over candidate code edits gated by tests: AlphaEvolve (DeepMind 2025), FunSearch, evolutionary code search. How tests-as-fitness lifts results.\n- Test-time compute scaling laws (e.g. OpenAI o1, DeepMind \"scaling test-time compute optimally\" Snell et al.) — when does spending more inference beat a bigger model.\n- Limits: when does best-of-N stop helping (verifier false positives, reward hacking, coverage ceiling, weak model never samples a correct solution at all).\n\nRun at least 4-5 searches. Fetch authoritative sources (arXiv, DeepMind blog for AlphaEvolve/FunSearch, the Large Language Monkeys paper). Cross-check numbers.\n\nReturn a list of FALSIFIABLE CLAIMS each with: claim, number/detail, source URL. Flag conflicts. Do NOT write files. Return findings only as your final message.","subagent_type":"general-purpose","run_in_background":true},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9761,"cache_read_input_tokens":5811,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":9761,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":{"cache_miss_reason":{"type":"tools_changed","cache_missed_input_tokens":12531}}},"requestId":"req_011CcG1zzhXgWJa7ULL15JYW","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","type":"assistant","uuid":"c976fca9-53f6-489c-a8e6-5d6eea973c21","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:46.684Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
